  "title": "The Engine",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "id": "b0",
      "index": 0,
      "kind": "heading",
      "text": "The Engine",
      "level": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b1",
      "index": 1,
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "The principle is simple and elegant."
    },
    {
      "id": "b2",
      "index": 2,
      "kind": "figure",
      "src": "images/cycle.png",
      "alt": "four stroke cycle",
      "caption": "Figure 1. The four-stroke cycle."
    },
    {
      "id": "b3",
      "index": 3,
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "As shown in Figure 1, each stroke drives the next."
    },
    {
      "id": "b4",
      "index": 4,
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "The crankshaft then converts linear motion into rotation."
    },
    {
      "id": "b5",
      "index": 5,
      "kind": "pullquote",
      "text": "Simplicity is the soul of efficiency."
    },
    {
      "id": "b6",
      "index": 6,
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "Later designs improved on this; see Figure 2 for the variant."
    },
    {
      "id": "b7",
      "index": 7,
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "That variant fires every revolution."
    },
    {
      "id": "b8",
      "index": 8,
      "kind": "figure",
      "src": "images/variant.png",
      "alt": "two stroke variant",
      "caption": "Figure 2. The two-stroke variant."
    }
  ],
